highlights.description: KC: Participants reacting to the LVN browser before their conversation begins
KC: LVN: reactions to the browser
KC: Personal story about how we should live on this earth better
KC: I enjoy living in such a unique place where kids ride unicycles to school
KC: Valuing the civic culture in Wisconsin
KC: There is something about the Midwest that is important
KC: Inequity is what concerns us most
KC: I don't interact with people of color and I don't know how to change that
KC: I don't understand why Wisconsin has such horrible racial inequities
KC: We are upper middle class but I worry about our kids' economic security
KC: Our democracy is listing to one side but we will right the ship
KC: Exchange about how we are polarized along rural vs urban lines and have to address that, but then the divisiveness is manufactured and manipulated by money
KC: LVN: conversation about value of highlight played from the Hearth, and then broader discussion about apartment rates
KC: LVN: appreciation for a different kind of conversation, even during a dinner party
KC: There is nothing more important right now than getting people to vote, and politicians need to support the franchise

KC: How do we get our democracy unstuck? Politicians take risks? Work within the system? Hey Madison representatives, can you leap into an opportunity here?-- Would be great to play for a local elected official or candidate for office.

title: Near east side group of friends who share a love for the environment, Feb 23rd
